<subSubSection id="AD7155F974B11C335876CA77FCB4CE37" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="2B4AD2A26C43D5FF7EBDEDB6658F3021" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">Discussion.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="AF5561187079842801A0F70771B8F5BF" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">
<taxonomicName id="58A18E35745635AD0013CCC20734E188" baseAuthorityName="Mueller" baseAuthorityYear="1776" class="Insecta" family="Andrenidae" genus="Andrena" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Andrena nitida" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nitida">
<emphasis id="C7EC9FE385BD95F338B1AC94B128264A" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">Andrena nitida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was recorded from Morocco by 
<bibRefCitation id="301AC163326041E679324E473356A4AF" author="Warncke, K" journalOrPublisher="Mitteilungen aus dem Zoologischen Museum in Berlin" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" pagination="3 - 54" refId="B50" refString="Warncke, K, 1974. Beitrag zur Kenntnis und Verbreitung der Sandbienen in Nordafrika (Hymenoptera, Apoidea, Andrena). Mitteilungen aus dem Zoologischen Museum in Berlin 50: 3 - 54" title="Beitrag zur Kenntnis und Verbreitung der Sandbienen in Nordafrika (Hymenoptera, Apoidea, Andrena)." volume="50" year="1974">Warncke (1974)</bibRefCitation>
under the name 
<taxonomicName id="2B630AB495D47AAE0E05E1FBD84ECAA5" class="Insecta" family="Andrenidae" genus="Andrena" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Andrena nitida subsp. mixtura" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="nitida" subSpecies="mixtura">
<emphasis id="BA0A4EF2A9BBC9F3396A969BA1631D43" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">Andrena nitida mixtura</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Warncke, 1967. This subspecies was described from Portugal and Spain under the name 
<taxonomicName id="7BDC9EC95543FEA7261A60E099C330D4" authorityName="Smith" authorityYear="1853" class="Insecta" family="Andrenidae" genus="Andrena" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Andrena limata" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="limata">
<emphasis id="9B191405FA77939BEE5FA25FF049816C" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">Andrena limata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Smith, 1853 
<taxonomicName id="3269DE562B14EFFEA47EF15F0940C18D" class="Insecta" family="Andrenidae" genus="Andrena" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="mixtura" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mixtura">
<emphasis id="62E96085E1D19E5246B5DA04C62B7C2F" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">mixtura</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Warncke, 1967). However, Warncke transferred this subspecies into combination with 
<taxonomicName id="CE17B91EEE423AC1BF38B6B273A88171" genus="A." lsidName="A. nitida" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" rank="species" species="nitida">
<emphasis id="878F58806E6C1AAEB065370A3D6A1001" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">A. nitida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation id="DBED5B93CAE95A9B0B50212ADD7A547B" author="Warncke, K" journalOrPublisher="Mitteilungen aus dem Zoologischen Museum in Berlin" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" pagination="3 - 54" refId="B50" refString="Warncke, K, 1974. Beitrag zur Kenntnis und Verbreitung der Sandbienen in Nordafrika (Hymenoptera, Apoidea, Andrena). Mitteilungen aus dem Zoologischen Museum in Berlin 50: 3 - 54" title="Beitrag zur Kenntnis und Verbreitung der Sandbienen in Nordafrika (Hymenoptera, Apoidea, Andrena)." volume="50" year="1974">Warncke 1974</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="487E2989B1DBF263B2B7262CDC5667BA" author="Warncke, K" journalOrPublisher="Eos" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" pagination="119 - 223" refId="B53" refString="Warncke, K, 1976. Die Bienengattung Andrena F., 1775, in Iberien (Hym. Apidae). Teil B. Eos 50: 119 - 223" title="Die Bienengattung Andrena F., 1775, in Iberien (Hym. Apidae). Teil B." volume="50" year="1976">1976</bibRefCitation>
) without any apparent justification. Examination of the type series of 
<taxonomicName id="6398C3F081B08F4DE60F5BB61AAD8711" genus="A." lsidName="A. n. subsp. mixtura" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" rank="subSpecies" species="n." subSpecies="mixtura">
<emphasis id="340973E04CA6031DCF03CA5188D8E783" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">A. n. mixtura</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
shows that its original placement was justified based on its bivoltine behaviour and the darker colouration of its tergal and scopal hairs (
<bibRefCitation id="40E49B602468040D9C50898B1778EEC9" DOI="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.4790.2.1" author="Wood, TJ" journalOrPublisher="Zootaxa" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" pagination="201 - 228" refId="B61" refString="Wood, TJ, Cross, I, Baldock, DW, 2020a. Updates to the bee fauna of Portugal with the description of three new Iberian Andrena species (Hymenoptera: Apoidea: Anthophila). Zootaxa 4790: 201 - 228, DOI: https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.4790.2.1" title="Updates to the bee fauna of Portugal with the description of three new Iberian Andrena species (Hymenoptera: Apoidea: Anthophila)." url="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.4790.2.1" volume="4790" year="2020 a">Wood et al. 2020a</bibRefCitation>
), and that therefore records of 
<taxonomicName id="4475B0088A98C9166D9D5E870E193880" genus="A." lsidName="A. n. subsp. mixtura" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" rank="subSpecies" species="n." subSpecies="mixtura">
<emphasis id="54727CD4B0D0ECFA7458213686E3A357" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">A. n. mixtura</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from North Africa (none of which are part of the type series) refer to 
<taxonomicName id="543730DE0C7FA56AC92AE651AA612FEE" genus="A." lsidName="A. limata" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" rank="species" species="limata">
<emphasis id="70C13501E3D9DE9A5D3EB1684FEBAE04" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">A. limata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and that 
<taxonomicName id="1A6AB50ECA33C27E896824321FF1C1C6" genus="A." lsidName="A. nitida" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" rank="species" species="nitida">
<emphasis id="B614EF5ABAF2CB9B3DE0A31B7018FC3E" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">A. nitida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
should be removed from the Moroccan list.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
